ewcommand{\F}{\mathcal{F}} \let\phi\varphi $ The motivation is that we want to solve the PDE called the heat equation where the time change is the average change in space. The Laplacian $\Delta$ models "average change" in space. Thus, the heat equation is \[ \partial_t u_t(x) = \Delta u_t(x) \] with initial value $u_0(x) = u(x)$. The Laplacian $\Delta$ models "average change". Consider a symmetric random walk with density $p_t(x)$ with time $t$ in discrete steps.
